   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">First rule of this deck -> Have fun, dagnabbit!<br>
<br>
Magi - Gogor. With him, it&#39;s best to go second if you can at all help it.. If you&#39;re first, then your foe knows a gravel-storm is coming and can deploy their creatures accordingly. Unless you pull a second pair of Goggles and a creature to use them, save the eyewear for Trygar and his &#39;fufs. Depending how things are progressing, you may want to save the Arboll for Trygar, as well. Pumped up pylofufs can be of nightmarish proportions.<br>
<br>
- Trygar comes out second, bringing with him a Pylofuf, his Bwisp, and a pair of Tunneler&#39;s Boots. His mission is simple... set up an ambush with Pylofufs, and or Tunnel Hyren&#39;d Parmalags, then simply use the burrow effect to wreck havoc.<br>
When / if Trygar falls, use his Avenger to drop a Parmalag (The small kind) for Radget<br>
<br>
- Radget comes third.. There are a number of things you can do with this parmalag-friendly magi.. For one, she starts with an Impact. Lovely if you have an Ormagon in hand, and your foe is also on their third magi. Even if not, with her power of Refresh and the hand full of Parmalags you should have, Radget shouldn&#39;t give you too much trouble.<br>
<br>
Specific Cards - <br>
Ghost Bwisp - Pretty much tech against Corrupt.. Otherwise, only useful if you have a Warrior&#39;s Boots to go with them..<br>
<br>
Gorgle&#39;s Curse - Got a non-discardable creature out there? Curse it, then fini off with a Resonate or Thunderquake a couple others with it.<br>
<br>
Bottomless Pit - Thunderquake a few creatures down into range, and send them straight down..<br>
<br>
Burrow - Use these to protect your Tunnel Hyrens, since their effect isn&#39;t self-centered..<br>
<br>
Cave Hyren - Two words -> Energy Transfer. Use these guys to add energy to the ones that need it. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
